data.title: A Great Orator [The Rt Hon Herbert Henry Asquith] by XIT: (1910) Art / Print / Poster
data.meta_description: 1910 - Condition: Good - VANITY FAIR SPY CARTOON Herbert Henry Asquith 'A Great Orator' Politics 1910. Antique chromolithograph (colour) Vanity Fair "Spy" cartoon/caricature print; XIT (17 March 1910). Picture size 19 x 33cm (7.5 x 13 inches); Overall page size approximately 25 x 37cm (10 x 15 inches). Condition: Good. A copy of the original biographical notes published with the print will be provided. There is nothing printed on the reverse side, which is plain. ASQUITH Rt. Hon. H H. Prime Minister. Born Morley Yorkshire September 12th 1852. Educated Balliol. Became a lawyer. Entered Parliament 1886. Home Secretary 1892. Chancellor of the Exchequer. Shown at the Dispatch Box. By XIT. (Politics) Picture size 19 x 33cm (7.5 x 13 inches); Overall page size approximately 25 x 37cm (10 x 15 inches) - A Great Orator [The Rt Hon Herbert Henry Asquith]
